TITLE: Configuring Formbricks Helm Chart Values
DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration defines the values for deploying Formbricks using Helm. It includes settings for autoscaling, deployment specifications, database configurations, and service definitions. The configuration allows for customization of resource allocation, security settings, and integration with external services.
SOURCE: https://github.com/formbricks/formbricks/blob/main/helm-chart/README.md#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
autoscaling:
  enabled: true
  minReplicas: 1
  maxReplicas: 10
  metrics:
    - type: "Resource"
      resource:
        name: "cpu"
        target:
          type: "Utilization"
          averageUtilization: 60
    - type: "Resource"
      resource:
        name: "memory"
        target:
          type: "Utilization"
          averageUtilization: 60

deployment:
  image:
    repository: "ghcr.io/formbricks/formbricks"
    pullPolicy: "IfNotPresent"
  resources:
    limits:
      memory: "2Gi"
    requests:
      cpu: "1"
      memory: "1Gi"
  probes:
    livenessProbe:
      httpGet:
        path: "/health"
        port: 3000

postgresql:
  enabled: true
  auth:
    database: "formbricks"
    username: "formbricks"

redis:
  enabled: true
  architecture: "standalone"

ingress:
  enabled: false
  hosts:
    - host: "k8s.formbricks.com"
      paths:
        - path: "/"
          pathType: "Prefix"
          serviceName: "formbricks"

service:
  enabled: true
  type: "ClusterIP"
```

